	◦	Azure SQL
	•	BASE:
	◦	Cosmos DB
GCP
	•	ACID:
	◦	Cloud Spanner
	•	BASE:
	◦	Bigtable
	◦	Firestore

10. Interview Perspective
How to Explain It Simply
Say:
“ACID ensures correctness inside a database. BASE enables scalability in distributed systems. CAP explains why we must trade consistency for availability when failures occur.”
Then explain:
	•	Which one your system uses
	•	Why that choice was made
	•	What tradeoffs were accepted

What Interviewers Look For
	•	Clear understanding of tradeoffs
	•	Ability to apply concepts practically
	•	Awareness of distributed system behavior
	•	Business-driven reasoning

Common Mistakes
	•	Thinking ACID and BASE are competitors
	•	Applying ACID everywhere
	•	Ignoring network partitions
	•	Assuming strong consistency is always better

Final Takeaway
	•	ACID = correctness
	•	BASE = scalability
	•	CAP = reality of distributed systems
Great architects:
	•	Use ACID where correctness matters
	•	Use BASE where scale matters
	•	Use CAP to make informed tradeoffs
	•	Design systems, not theories
